     ". \[Rho] can also be a vector in ket expression."
    }],ExpressionUUID->"fec8a901-a5fc-4b63-8e98-b851769ff15f"]},
   {"", Cell[TextData[{
     Cell[BoxData[
      RowBox[{
       TemplateBox[{
         Cell[
          TextData["VonNeumannEntropy"]], 
         "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/VonNeumannEntropy", 
         "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
        "PackageLink",
        BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"], "[", 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TR"], ",", 
        StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TR"]}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "8e8be256-0dba-46d5-bbee-6b677e00d17b"],
     "\[LineSeparator]returns the quantum relative entropy of the mixed state \
\[Rho] with respect to \[Sigma]. \[Rho] and \[Sigma] may be an operator \
(mixed state) or ket vector (pure state)."
    }],ExpressionUUID->"4f24ef41-a5b0-4087-9494-24847f0d308e"]},
   {"", Cell[TextData[{
     Cell[BoxData[
      RowBox[{
       TemplateBox[{
         Cell[
          TextData["VonNeumannEntropy"]], 
         "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/VonNeumannEntropy", 
         "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
        "PackageLink",
        BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"], "[", 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"], ",", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          SubscriptBox[
           StyleBox["s", "TI"], 
           StyleBox["1", "TR"]], ",", 
          SubscriptBox[
           StyleBox["s", "TI"], 
           StyleBox["2", "TR"]], ",", 
          StyleBox["\[Ellipsis]", "TR"]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "82cfa4a8-0bd3-4ecd-bc59-b9a497e26b34"],
     " or ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      RowBox[{
       TemplateBox[{
         Cell[
          TextData["VonNeumannEntropy"]], 
         "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/VonNeumannEntropy", 
         "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
        "PackageLink",
        BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"], "[", 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TR"], ",", 
        StyleBox["\[Sigma]", "TR"], ",", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          SubscriptBox[
           StyleBox["s", "TI"], 
           StyleBox["1", "TR"]], ",", 
          SubscriptBox[
           StyleBox["s", "TI"], 
           StyleBox["2", "TR"]], ",", 
          StyleBox["\[Ellipsis]", "TR"]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "60d72e26-a39d-4e63-938b-26b76b9f5240"],
     "\[LineSeparator]allows to specify otherwise unclear systems by ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox[
         StyleBox["s", "TI"], 
         StyleBox["1", "TR"]], ",", 
        SubscriptBox[
         StyleBox["s", "TI"], 
         StyleBox["2", "TR"]], ",", 
        StyleBox["\[Ellipsis]", "TR"]}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "906996c2-de35-460c-b63c-b5b38383a39c"],
     ". For example, when \[Rho] and/or \[Sigma] is a density operator acting \
non-trivially only on parts of the total system, there is no way to figure \
out the ingredient systems from the expression for \[Rho] (or \[Sigma]) alone."
    }],ExpressionUUID->"bae9ccc9-7481-4ca5-986c-c1648f470f5d"]}
